          <p></p>
          <h3 id="Usemacrosandadddynamiccontenttoyourpages-UsingJIRA?CreateanddisplaydynamicJIRAissuesinConfluence">
            <strong>
              Using JIRA? Create and display dynamic JIRA issues in Confluence
            </strong>
          </h3>
          <p>
            If your Confluence site is connected to a JIRA application, you can both create and display your JIRA issues without having to leave Confluence using the
            <a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ConfCloud/JIRA+Issues+Macro" rel="nofollow">
              JIRA Issues Macro
            </a>
            . It automatically updates to display the current status of your issues. You can connect Confluence to any JIRA application, including JIRA Software and JIRA Service Desk.
          </p>
          <p></p>
          <p>
            <span>
              <img src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/33463/jirachart.png?api=v2">
            </span>
          </p>
